Through this academic ransomware simulation project, I gained hands-on experience in:

- Understanding how ransomware locates and processes files
- Learning the fundamentals of XOR-based encryption behavior (simulated safely)
- Using Windows API functions for file operations
- Renaming and manipulating files programmatically
- Simulating malware warning messages and access restrictions
- Structuring a malware-like workflow for defensive analysis
- Improving my understanding of secure coding principles and safe testing practices
- Strengthening my malware analysis and threat modeling mindset
